66
00:04:31.830 --> 00:04:33.080
It is also very simple.

67
00:04:33.720 --> 00:04:39.680
Take each digit or character from hexadecimal value and replace it with its 4 bit binary value 

68
00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:43.840
So see an example. We have the hexadecimal value FD

69
00:04:44.290 --> 00:04:48.070
So write the corresponding 4 bit binary of F and D. 

70
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:53.740
for F it is 1111 and for D it is 1101

71
00:04:54.720 --> 00:05:02.200
So for the hexadecimal number FD, the equivalent binary value is 11111101. 

